The paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms for classification of microcirculation images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of unsupervised convolutional autoencoder also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the potential diagnostic application of the classifier, which could fall under medical engineering (cs.ME) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with sepsis, a medical condition, which could also suggest the involvement of bioinformatics (cs.BIO) sub-category.
